# Paper Readiness

## 0. Role Of This File

This file tracks the gaps between current results and a writeup (README, technical report, or paper): for each claim the writeup wants to make, what evidence is still missing. Candidate experiments that would close these gaps live in `docs/project/backlog/layer-backlog.md` and the shortlist in `docs/project/backlog/active-issues.md`. Writing guidance and the safe-claim boundary live in `docs/writing/paper-writing-guide.md`.

## 1. Claims Wanted Versus Evidence

For each claim a writeup would want to make, record the evidence still needed and its status. This is the bridge from `docs/writing/paper-writing-guide.md` section 4 (what is safe to claim) to the backlog (what {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} would make it safe). None recorded yet; the row below is a marked example. Status is one of: not started, in progress, or supported (evidence in `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`).

| claim wanted | evidence needed | status |
|---|---|---|
| (example) method beats the baseline | head-to-head result on the chosen benchmark, same budget | not started |

A claim is only writeup-ready when its status is supported and the evidence sits inside the safe-claim boundary. Until then it stays in future work, not in the abstract.
